    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dormers whose eaves lines are parallel to the eaves lines of the main roof instead of being gabled; provide more attic space than gabled dormers. Dormers whose eaves lines are parallel to the eaves lines of the main roof instead of being gabled; provide more attic space than gabled dormers.</Note_Text>
